---
import PageIntro from "@web/components/PageIntro.astro";
import BaseLayout from "@web/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import {
  buildPortfolioPageMetadata,
  getPortfolioBrochurePage,
  getPortfolioSocialLinkByPlatform,
} from "@web/lib/portfolio-brochure";

const { page } = await getPortfolioBrochurePage("privacy");
const metadata = buildPortfolioPageMetadata(page);
const emailLink = getPortfolioSocialLinkByPlatform("email");
---

<BaseLayout metadata={metadata}>
  <PageIntro
    subheading={page.subheading}
    title={page.title}
    intro={page.intro}
  />

  <section
    aria-labelledby="privacy-content-heading"
    class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-12 sm:px-8"
    role="region"
  >
    <h2 id="privacy-content-heading" class="sr-only">
      Privacy and consent details
    </h2>
    <div class="prose-zinc prose max-w-none">
      <p>
        This site is a static portfolio and professional site for Guy Romelle
        Magayano. It can load Google Analytics, Vercel Web Analytics, and Vercel
        Speed Insights when those services are configured for the deployed site.
        It can also use Sentry to report application errors and performance
        traces.
      </p>

      <h2>Information handled today</h2>
      <p>
        The site can receive standard hosting logs such as request path, user
        agent, approximate timestamp, referrer, and IP address. Those logs are
        used for security, debugging, abuse prevention, and deployment
        operations. If you email me or open an external profile, the information
        you provide is handled by your email provider or that external service.
      </p>

      <h2>Analytics and measurement</h2>
      <p>
        When Google Analytics is enabled, the site measures page views,
        navigation clicks, outbound profile links, direct contact clicks,
        article search terms, scroll depth, section views, and visible
        capability, work, note, lab, or call-to-action cards. The purpose is to
        understand which pages, capabilities, notes, and contact paths help
        visitors evaluate the portfolio and request work.
      </p>
      <p>
        Vercel Web Analytics can measure aggregate page views and referrers, and
        Vercel Speed Insights can measure web performance signals such as page
        load and Core Web Vitals. Those measurements are used to understand site
        health and improve performance.
      </p>
      <p>
        Sentry can collect error messages, stack traces, browser and device
        context, request headers and IP address where available, page URL,
        release, deployment environment, application logs, custom metrics,
        release-health session status, sampled performance traces, and sampled
        session replay data. That data is used to diagnose broken pages,
        JavaScript failures, and deployment regressions.
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and local storage</h2>
      <p>
        Google Analytics may use cookies or similar browser storage to measure
        visits and engagement. Sentry Session Replay may also use browser
        storage for sampled debugging sessions and error-session capture. This
        site does not add advertising pixels.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this privacy and consent baseline can be sent through
        the contact page
        {
          emailLink ? (
            <>
              {" "}
              or by emailing{" "}
              <a href={emailLink.href}>Guy Romelle Magayano directly</a>
            </>
          ) : null
        }
        .
      </p>

      <p>
        <strong>Last updated:</strong> May 1, 2026.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
